How We Protect Your Information - Security and Passwords
User sencial App Development takes what it believes to be commercially reasonable physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect Personal Information. However, since no security system is impenetrable and “perfect security” does not exist on the Internet, we cannot guarantee the security of Personal Information or Browsing Information.

You should choose a password that is not easy to guess, and does not use words that you would find in a dictionary. Do not disclose your password to any other person. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your password and account, and we will attribute activities that occur using your account information (e.g., through the use of your password) to you. If you suspect that your password has been compromised, contact us immediately at  ashwin.nandihalli@gmail.com.

Compromise of Personal Information
In the event that Personal Information is compromised as a result of a breach of security, User sencial App Development will promptly notify those persons whose Personal Information has been compromised, in accordance with the notification procedures set forth in this Privacy Policy, or as otherwise required by applicable law. In the event that we or our Service suffers a data security breach that requires us to provide you with notice, such as under applicable law, you consent to allow us to provide you with such notice by sending an email to the primary email address that is associated with your account.
Children’s Privacy Policy
User sencial App Development makes commercially reasonable efforts to ensure users privacy Protection and no Personal Information is collected or solicited inside the app Kannada kali. App progress may be stored remotely to facilitate multi-device play and allow parents/caregivers to view their child’s progress. Kannada kali contains no external links to third-party websites or services.

Kannada kali is directed at users of all ages, including children. We encourage parents/caregivers and teachers to supervise their child or student’s use of the Apps. Simply downloading Kannada kali to your devices does not trigger the collection of any personally identifiable information. We collect only a unique device identifier (a 40-character long mathematical code, called a “hex value”). This device identifier only allows User sencial App Development  to send necessary administrative updates to your tablet (such as software updates and administrative messages). No Personal Information is collected by User sencial App Development through the App download process or during the use of app. We may collect analytics data (which does not contain Personal Information) from your use of the Service in order to offer and develop the Service, and we may collect information such as age, grade, textbook, and name from parents/caregivers as part of your use of the Apps and the Service and the creation of your user profile.

*For Beta Testing and Playtesting Only*
This section provides information to parents who sign up to participate in our Beta Testing or Playtesting programs. It explains how we may collect, use, and share Personal Information from parents/caregivers and from their children in the context of using our Service for Beta Testing and Playtesting only.

Personal Information We Collect from Children for Beta Testing or Playtesting
With parents/caregivers authorization, we may collect the following Personal Information from children in the context of using our Service for Beta Testing or Playtesting:

Image captures (photographs) and/or audio captures, depending on the project, that may contain a child’s image or voice.
Information about the child’s activities on our Service, such as levels played, buttons pressed, and puzzles completed.
We may collect info from Parents/caregivers email addresses, last name, telephone numbers, or other relevant shipping information.
And account and profile information, such as child’s reading level, words they may struggle with;
Information on devices used to play, such as device model number, operating system; and
Persistent identifiers, such as IP address.

Personal Information Uses for Beta Testing and Playtesting
We use the Personal Information we collect from Parents/caregivers and children for Beta Testing and Playtesting only for purposes necessary to facilitate providing the Service or maintain and analyze the functioning of the Service, such as for product optimization purposes.

Personal Information Disclosures for Beta for Beta Testing and Playtesting
We disclose the Personal Information we collect from Parents/caregivers and children for Beta Testing and Playtesting only to our affiliates, third-party service providers, engineers, and researchers solely for the purposes described above (such as for product optimization purposes).

Requests to Access and Delete a Child’s Information Collected for Beta Testing or Playtesting
Parents/caregivers of children who participate in Beta Testing or Playtesting may request to review the Personal Information collected from their child, direct us to delete the Personal Information that we have collected from their child, and refuse to permit our further collection or use of the Personal Information collected from their child. To do so, please reach out to us at ashwin.nandihalli@gmail.com

